{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"revenued-thickset-dassie","description":"## Why\nThe `code_review` artifact (per Gerrit change/revision) persists findings today but is WRITE-ONLY: there is no reader analogous to plan-review's `latest_review_result`, and the payload records only a diff-text hash, not the reviewed code STATE. The novelty convergence gate needs (a) prior SURFACED findings to score against, and (b) a content-addressed record of what code was reviewed, to gate the floor per file.\n\n## What\n- Extend the `code_review_result_v1` payload (src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py `build_payload`) with:\n  - `session_id` (nullable; set for local reviews),\n  - `deps`: a per-reviewed-file content-hash map `{path: sha256}`, computed by REUSING plan-review's `attest.dependency_hashes` / `_hash_file` (raw file-bytes sha256, with the `absent` sentinel so create/delete is detectable). Scope = the review's changed_files (and cited-file paths).\n- Add a reader `latest_code_review_result(key)` (typed key: `session:<id>` or `change:<id>`) that returns the most-recent artifact's SURFACED findings (decision in {block, advisory}) plus its `deps` map. Mirror `latest_review_result`'s best-effort, never-raises, schema-guarded, walk-back-over-unusable posture. SURFACED-ONLY is mandatory (see old-frilly-plankton) so dropped findings never re-enter the novelty prior set.\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py (payload + reader).\n- Compute `deps` centrally in the gate (produce_code_review_verdict) so BOTH local and the Gerrit voter path get it via the existing emit.\n- Out of scope: local persistence wiring (its own story), the region_gated_floor consumer (its own story).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `build_payload` records `session_id` and a `{path: sha256}` deps map reusing `attest._hash_file`/`dependency_hashes`.\n- [ ] `latest_code_review_result(key)` returns SURFACED-only prior findings + the deps map, keyed by typed `session:`/`change:` key; never raises; schema-guarded to `code_review_result_v1`.\n- [ ] Unit tests: surfaced-only filtering, typed-key isolation (a `session:` key never returns a `change:` artifact and vice versa), malformed/absent → None.\n- [ ] The deps map is computed once in the gate and flows to both local and Gerrit emits.","id":"c639-4122-58d9-4dc2","parent_id":"374d-9aaf-7d5b-4331","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Code-review finding-memory reader + artifact payload (session_id + reviewed-file content-hash map)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783625841064309001,"uuid":"2268e793-fa5a-493c-b7ff-526896a0e5e0"}